    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Keep Watching the Skies? How About the Sidewalks?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Diana Binder letter on January 26 article says she stopped spitting chewing gum on sidewalks when brand new pair of shoes was ruined by wad of gum</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I shamefully admit that I used to routinely spit gum on the sidewalks of New York (''Out, Damned Spot,'' Jan. 26). But no more. About 15 years ago I walked out of a shoe store wearing beautiful, brand new black leather shoes.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I shamefully admit that I used to routinely spit gum on the sidewalks of New York (''Out, Damned Spot,'' Jan. 26). But no more. About 15 years ago I walked out of a shoe store wearing beautiful, brand new black leather shoes.</p>
        <p>One block from the store I looked down to see one of those beautiful shoes entrapped by a huge wad of very sticky gum. Ruined shoe. Reformed spitter.</p>
        <p>DIANA BINDER  Kips Bay</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
